---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Profile" description="Developer profile for Min, author of Dev with Min.">
  <header class="page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Developer profile</p>
    <h1>Min</h1>
    <p>
      I use this space to keep a direct record of how I learn, build, operate, and think about
      software systems.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="profile-direction-title">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <h2 id="profile-direction-title">Direction</h2>
        <p>
          This profile will evolve into the human side of the blog: interests, engineering values,
          current focus, and the thread connecting projects to writing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid card-grid--two">
      <article class="section-card">
        <h3>What I write about</h3>
        <p>
          Homelab infrastructure, DevOps practice, AI agent usage, setup details, and CS philosophy.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="section-card">
        <h3>How I want it to feel</h3>
        <p>Honest, practical, readable, and useful as a history of developer experience.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
